cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this software or its accompanying paper, please cite both the
  ACM conference paper (preferred-citation block, below) and this software
  artifact.
type: software
title: >-
  VGAC: A Full-Stack GPU Cluster Observability Platform with Calibration-Gated
  Predictive Intelligence
abstract: >-
  Reproducible scientific-software artifact accompanying the PEARC '26 paper
  "VGAC". Includes the calibration-gated prediction pipeline (universal
  feature schema, isotonic post-hoc calibration, four-tier qualification, PSI
  and temporal-ECE drift detection, sliding-window recalibration), policy
  translation layer (gpu_ext bridge, generator, inference router), routing
  simulation harness, sample data for four cluster environments
  (EKS-Dec, Slurm with DCGM, Alibaba GPU trace 2020/2023, Google Borg 2019),
  benchmark artifacts, architecture/methodology documentation, and a single
  Jupyter notebook that regenerates every figure in the paper.
